qas.question: What title was the fourth Dalai Lama granted?
Who was the fourth Dalai Lama?
When did the Wanli Emperor grant the title Master of Vajradhara to Yonten Gyatso?
Who did the Wanli Emperor invite to Beijing in 1616?
Why didn't Yonten Gyatso make it to Beijing?

context: Chen states that the fourth Dalai Lama <a1_0><a3_0>Yonten Gyatso<a3_0/><a1_0/> was granted the title "<a0_0>Master of Vajradhara<a0_0/>" and an official seal by the Wanli Emperor in <a2_0>1616<a2_0/>. This was noted in the Biography of the Fourth Dalai Lama, which stated that one Soinam Lozui delivered the seal of the Emperor to the Dalai Lama. The Wanli Emperor had invited Yonten Gyatso to Beijing in 1616, but just like his predecessor <a4_0>he died<a4_0/> before being able to make the journey.
